For good programming skills, you must:

Develop a close understanding between the hardware and the software!

Read status of a pin
Control status of a pin

Learn different methods for operating the hardware
- Turn on/off
- Flash on/off
- Pulse on/off
- Send codes

Learn different methods for reading an input
- Measure status of a pin
- Measure change time of a pin
- Measure group of pins

Communication methods
- Synchronous - Shift Register
- Asynchronous - RS232

Control Program Flow
- Decisions
- Loops
- Counters

